# Database Design Guidelines

Directives only. No full scripts, schemas, or pipelines.

---

## Relational Design Directives

### Normalisation

- Normalise to 3NF by default; remove transitive dependencies and repeating groups
- Keep each table focused on a single entity; use junction tables for many-to-many
- Denormalise only when: read-heavy workloads justify write cost, joins are proven bottlenecks, or a dominant query pattern is stable
- Document denormalisation decisions; keep them reversible

### Schema Structure

- Use UUIDs or surrogate keys when natural keys are unstable or composite
- Prefer `TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE` for timestamps
- Add `created_at` and `updated_at` on all mutable tables
- Use `ON DELETE CASCADE` / `ON DELETE SET NULL` only when the business rule is explicit

