## Indexing Strategy

### Index Types and When to Use

- **Primary key** â€” Automatic; unique per row; prefer clustered where supported
- **Single-column** â€” Unique lookups (e.g. `email`), foreign keys, frequently filtered columns
- **Composite** â€” Multi-column filters and sorts; order by selectivity (most selective first)
- **Partial** â€” Subset of rows (e.g. `WHERE is_active = true`); reduces size and maintenance
- **Text search** â€” GIN/GiST for full-text; B-tree for prefix/suffix

### Indexing Rules

- Index foreign keys used in joins
- Avoid indexing low-cardinality columns alone
- Avoid over-indexing write-heavy tables
- Run `ANALYZE` after bulk loads; schedule `VACUUM` / `REINDEX` where needed
- Monitor usage; drop unused indexes

```sql
CREATE INDEX idx_users_active_created ON users(is_active, created_at);
CREATE INDEX idx_users_email ON users(email) WHERE is_active = true;
```

