## Data Integrity

### Constraints

- Use `NOT NULL` for required fields
- Use `CHECK` for domain rules (e.g. `status IN ('draft', 'published')`)
- Use `UNIQUE` for natural keys
- Add cross-column checks where rules span columns (e.g. `published_at` required when `status = 'published'`)

### Foreign Keys

- Always define foreign keys for referential integrity
- Choose `ON DELETE` / `ON UPDATE` behaviour explicitly

### Soft Delete Pattern

- Use `deleted_at` column; filter `deleted_at IS NULL` in all queries
- Add partial indexes for active rows
- Ensure parent references don't point to soft-deleted children

